            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This is essentially asking for inlay hints / virtual text to act like floating windows. The entire purpose of virtual text is that it's not part of the buffer. And for that reason it should be used sparingly--I agree that non-interactive text is rarely a \"feature\".\n\nBeing able to interact with virtual text would require a mappings \"sub-mode\" or something like that (which again is just redundant with floating windows).\n\n# Proposal\n\nIntroduce a command that temporarily toggles all virtual text into floating windows. Then it can be toggled back.",
